                    </p>
                </div>
                <div id="item-2-2">
                    <h4 class="display-6 mt-5 pt-2">Modding</h4>
                    <hr><p class="fs-5">
                        A custom level pack's data is stored in a <b><i>".lep"</i></b> project file. This file contains all of the level pack's data, including the level pack's title, subtitle, author, level names etc.
                        In addition to the <b><i>".lep"</i></b> file, a level pack also contains a <b><i>"maps"</i></b> folder. This folder contains all of the level data and story segments.
                    </p>
                    <p class="fs-5">
                        To install or test a custom level pack, inside your game folder go to <b>"Pandemonium FPS_Data/StreamingAssets/"</b>
                        and place the level pack's <b><i>".lep"</i></b> file and <b><i>"maps"</i></b> folder inside the "StreamingAssets" folder.
                    </p>
                    <p class="fs-5">
                        Make sure you only have one <b><i>".lep"</i></b> file inside the <b>"StreamingAssets"</b> folder at a time.
                        Otherwise, the game will not be able to load the level pack.
                    </p>
